101. A singular verb is frequently used with two or mbre sub- jects: 3, 16, 29 ff. rivus aquae silvaque . . . segetis certa fides . . . fallit.

102. The future indicative is occasionally used with permissive or hortatory force: 1, 7, 1 laudabunt alii claram Rhodon, ‘others may praise,' etc. ; 1, 12, 57 ff. te minor lamm reget aequus orbem, etc„ ‘let him rule,' etc.
